<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="390" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Recruiting/224:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-13T19:00:00-04:00">June
                                        13, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>368. Your 650, June 4. There is no provision of American law
                                prohibiting the enlistment in China of American citizens in the
                                armed forces of Great Britain. However attention is called to
                                provisions of section 401 (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) Nationality Act of 1940.<note n="13" xml:id="d390fn13">Approved October 14, 1940; 54 Stat.
                                    1137.</note> American citizens enlisted in armed forces of Great
                                Britain who proceed through combat areas violate section 3 of the
                                Neutrality Act; also section 5 if they proceed on a belligerent
                                vessel.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>